{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-page-js","path":"/news/new-standard-pottery-studies-archaeology-2016/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Published in June 2016, this guidance document was compiled by the three period-specific\npottery study groups (PCRG, SGRP, MPRG) with the aim of creating the first, comprehensive,\ninclusive standard for working with pottery.</p>\n<p>The Standard is intended for use in all types of archaeological project, including\nthose run by community groups, professional contractors and research institutions.\nThis standard has been published by the <a href=\"http://www.medievalpottery.org.uk/\">Medieval Pottery Research Group</a>\non behalf of the <a href=\"https://www.prehistoricpottery.org/\">Prehistoric Ceramics Research Group</a>,\nthe <a href=\"http://romanpotterystudy.org/\">Study Group for Roman Pottery</a> and the <a href=\"http://www.medievalpottery.org.uk/\">Medieval Pottery Research Group</a>.</p>\n<p>The text was written by Alistair Barclay and David Knight (PCRG); Paul Booth and Jane Evans (SGRP); Duncan H. Brown and Imogen Wood (MPRG).</p>\n<p>Development and production of this standard was funded by grant-aid from <a href=\"https://historicengland.org.uk/images-books/publications/standard-for-pottery-studies-in-archaeology/\">Historic England</a>.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 220px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 141.1042944785276%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/00b04a67180392dd9016bdbf16bc1db1/98307/pottery-studies-image.webp 163w,\n/static/00b04a67180392dd9016b